Observations:¶

All 3 dataframes has same set of column names in the same order. The columns represent 6 biomechanics attributes dervied from the shape and orientation of the condition to the patients body part. normal dataframe has 100 rows and 7 columns typeh dataframe has 60 rows and 7 columns types dataframe has 150 rows and 7 columns

Since the columns are same in all 3 dataframes, we can combine these 3 dataframes into a single dataframe.

  • P_tilt has less correlation with P_radius and S_slope

    print("classification  Matrix:\n",classification_report(y_test,predicted_labels))

def getAccuracy(testSet, predictions):
    correct = 0
    for x in range(len(testSet)):
        if testSet[x]==predictions[x]:
            correct += 1
    return (correct/float(len(testSet))) * 100.0

def rbf_model(g,c):
    for gi in g:
        for ci in c:
            res={}
            clf_rbf = svm.SVC(kernel="rbf", gamma=gi, C=ci) 
            clf_rbf.fit(X_train, y_train.values.ravel())
            y_pred = clf_rbf.predict(X_test)
            acc=getAccuracy(y_test["LoanOnCard"].tolist(),y_pred)
            res["g"]=gi
            res["ci"]=ci
            res["acc"]=acc
            print(res)
